Title : Martin de Silva
Text : '''Richard Martin M. de Silva ''' (3 March 1903, in Galle &ndash; 12 August 1978) was a [[Ceylonese]] [[cricket]]er.  He was an all rounder, who represented Ceylon in the first ever first-class cricket match played in the country.<ref>[http://static.espncricinfo.com/db/ARCHIVE/1920S/1925-26/SL_LOCAL/OTHERS/ROOKWOOD-CEYLON-XI_LUCAS-BOMBAY-XI_12-13FEB1926.htmlDr J Rookwood's Ceylon XI v WE Lucas's Bombay XI]</ref> R. M. M. de Silva also played for the Ceylonese against the visiting [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] in  1927  and was one of the best [[all-rounder]]s of the [[Sinhalese Sports Club]]. He was educated at [[Richmond College (Sri Lanka)|Richmond College]] in [[Galle]], where he captained the college cricket team in 1921 and 1922.<ref>[http://richmondcollege.org/sports/cricket_3.html Richmond College Cricket] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504091134/http://richmondcollege.org/sports/cricket_3.html |date=2014-05-04 }}</ref> Later he served as a cricket coach for the school cricketers in Galle district.<ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2004/12/13/spo04.html Life and times in sports]</ref>

